Seven people have died in South Africa due to COVID-19. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa is one week into the national lockdown and medical practitioners are pleading with citizens to stay at home. Seven people have died in South Africa due to COVID-19. The number of people confirmed to be infected has climbed to 1,505. READ: Mkhize: SA can beat COVID-19 Some health workers at the University of Pretoria have put together this video with a clear message, please stay at home. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.